summary: Yon-Rogg’s Reasons For Not Shooting Carol during their first Meeting
title: Yon-Rogg’s Reasons For Not Shooting Carol during their first Meeting
body:
After Yon-Rogg brings down Carol and Mar-Vell’s ship, he immediately shoots Mar-Vell, but not Carol. Why? Let’s assume he has two objectives: Kill/Capture Mar-Vell and acquire the energy core.  

Carol was ignorant of Mar-Vell’s plans until about thirty seconds before Yon-Rogg shows up. Yon-Rogg has no way of knowing how read-in Carol is about Mar-Vell’s mission, and yet he quickly kills the one person who could definitely tell him what he wants to know. 

The only way this makes sense is if Yon-Rogg already realizes where the energy core is and is acting to prevent Mar-Vell from destroying it. Yon-Rogg knows about the energy core’s existence and he just witnessed the ship’s performance in their recent air battle. Taking that into account, it’s reasonable to assume he knew what Mar-Vell was up to when she aims her gun at the ship. 

Now we return to Carol and why she was spared. Carol is a Terran who was just assisting an enemy of the Kree. Why not immediately take her out?  Yon-Rogg’s question about the energy core can not be the answer, because as we just established, he had to know the energy core was in the downed ship. 

I’m inclined to think this was more a “Give me reason not to kill you” type deal. Trigger-happy Minn-Erva is there with him, so he’s going to need some justification to classify Carol a non-threat. If she “helps” him by telling him where the core is, he’s got an excuse not to pull the trigger on her. When she continues to threaten and impede his mission, he suggests he’s about to shoot her, but stops when she says “Wait, wait, wait!”.  He is too slow to stop her from blowing the core. If he wasn’t hesitant to shoot her, I don’t believe either of those things could have happened.

Why would Yon-Rogg be reluctant to kill someone who had just sided with an enemy of the Kree? It’s not a though she were a bystander/civilian. My guess is that he was impressed with her piloting skills and her bravery. I’d further speculate that’s why Carol ended up being trained as a Kree Warrior, rather than being put down, or handed over to Kree Scientists.

summary: It's okay if you can't but can you do headcanons for reader coming out to carol danvers as trans?
question: It's okay if you can't but can you do headcanons for reader coming out to carol danvers as trans?
answer:
• Completely by accident, you brought up being transgender in a conversation. You immediately regretted the words that spilled out of your mouth.
  • Carol slowly started to know new knowledge about the things she missed out on Earth. She also knew about transgender
  • You were on the verge of a panic attack, your chest started to tighten like bricks were thrown onto it while your heart began to quicken like you were running a relay race.
  • Carol blinked at you, she was blown by surprise. Carol’s expression changed from shocked to joy, her face softened.
  • She pecked her lips onto yours with pure passion and heaven, a show of acceptance.
  • You weakly chuckle and shove your body against hers, kissing her once again.
